<br>
I had no clarity, so I was trying to optimize my use of right click nukes(Boots of Bladecalling).  I managed to keep my mana regenerating the entire time.  There was no &quot;full mana&quot; time.  I decided to try to put Kindir and his sceptre/ancient spell into my shoes, just to see what I'd get.  <br>
<br>
I found that I cast BoBC 165 times(17 seconds per), sofb 81 times(5.8 per), and FoT 3 times (7 per).  For a moment let's ignore mana.  I spent 3295.8 seconds casting spells.  Kindir figured 12.1 seconds per cast cycle, and you could fit 272.4 of those cycles into the time I spent casting.  At 1500 damage per cycle that would be 408,000 damage.<br>
<br>
My resist rate was about 6%.  I think it is more than reasonable to assume crits would make up for this.  I think 408,000 is reasonable as far as resists are concerned.<br>
<br>
Ok to summarize the numbers(and add a couple of missing ones:<br>
<br>
Camp session:  7714 seconds<br>
Time main warrior spent in combat: 4707 seconds.<br>
Time spent casting spells: 3295.8 seconds.<br>
Damage dealt:  408,000<br>
DPS (vs. the Main Tank):  86.7<br>
DPS (vs. the total session):  52.9<br>
<br>
Now, my realized DPS versus the main tank was only 39.  The huge difference comes from two main sources.  First, we ruled out mana regeneration and assumed Kindir would be using the click nuke and mana nuke an equal amount, whereas I had no clarity and used my boots almost exclusively.  Second, the ancient nuke has a higher dps, which would allow for more click damage assuming it was able to equal the damage done by shock of fiery blades.<br>
<br>
We can't -know- how mana would have limited Kindir, but we could guess.  I'm going to assume 33% reduction in mana cost (21% spec, 12% focus item)..  Sorry, but I think that is being somewhat generous.  In order for him to maintain the 86.7 dps vs. the MT quoted above, he would need to have 51938 mana in 7714 seconds, which is 40 mana per tick.<br>
<br>
Figure 11.5 per tick if you had a horse (7714-3295.8 to figure out time spend medding) That's if medding is 20 mana per tick.<br>
<br>
Then 4 from TPP.<br>
Then 14 from KEI, we're at 29.5 per tick.<br>
<br>
10.5 per tick from rods and flowing thought.  (Maybe 5 from rods.. and hell even I have FT 6.)<br>
<br>
Not too tough IMO.  The only thing is the fairly generous focus item figure, but even then you'd only need another 4 FT to make up for it.<br>
<br>
In order to achieve 125 dps versus the MT using my amount of time spent casting, you'd have to spend a lot more mana though.  Where I had you nuking 272 times with the sceptre and 272 times with the ancient nuke, to deal 125 dps instead of 86.6 you'd have to nuke 440 times with the ancient and 150 times with the sceptre.  This would up the required mana regen to 65.<br>
<br>
<br>
If your pet was doing 75dps, then I would say yes, 200 dps relative to another melee is at least in the realm of possibility.<br>
<br>
200dps is only uptime dps though, this would not be sustainable to infinity.  Given the uptime/downtime ratio, the 200dps in combat would be only 122 sustained..   But umm imo 122 sustained is fricking insanely high anyway so /shrug.  <br>
<br>
Flaws I see with this hypothesis:<br>
<br>
1.  Theoretically, up to 4707 seconds could have been spent casting spells.  In my experience, it isn't feasible to cast nukes for 100% of combat time,  but others may experience differently.<br>
<br>
2.  Switching me out with someone dealing a higher DPS, you'd change the conditions of the group.  The effect this would have on the analysis is unknown to me.  Perhaps it would lead to more downtime, perhaps less, perhaps the same with more mobs killed.  Hard to say. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral>General</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.101<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href="http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html">JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

